| `test_v0_vocabulary_each_observed_at_least_once` | Across the suite, each entry of the §7 vocabulary is observed by at least one test. | 07 §7 |

This is implemented via a session-scoped fixture that records every
non-2xx response's `type`. The two assertions run as two pytest items
collected last in the session via `pytest-ordering`. (Pinned in
`conformance/pyproject.toml`.) The `test_no_internal_eden_error_type_for_auth`
scenario from the pre-review draft is dropped: chapter 07 §11-12 makes
auth informative.

