codex
1. Bug — [misbehaving_adapter.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/conformance/src/conformance/_meta/misbehaving_adapter.py:38): the startup-cleanup fix is still incomplete for partial proxy startup. If `proxy.start()` spins up the proxy thread/socket and then raises before returning, the `except` block only calls `super().stop()`, so the proxy itself is never stopped. Fix by initializing `proxy: MisbehaveProxy | None = None` before the `try`, and in the `except` path call `proxy.stop()` when it exists before tearing down the upstream adapter.

2. Risk — [check_citations.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/conformance/src/conformance/tools/check_citations.py:35) and [check_citations.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/conformance/src/conformance/tools/check_citations.py:126): the MUST-check is fixed, but the chapter-9 coverage guard is still weaker than the plan. It hardcodes group names/file names instead of reading `spec/v0/09-conformance.md §5`, and it treats “file has tests” as coverage rather than “group has at least one valid citing test.” That means chapter-9 drift is still not actually detected the way plan §I described. Fix by parsing the §5 index from chapter 9 and counting valid citations per group, not raw file presence.

3. Risk — [test_event_delivery.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/conformance/scenarios/test_event_delivery.py:103): the planned `test_subscribe_empty_batch_after_timeout` scenario was removed. I understand the rationale, but it is still a plan-adherence deviation from §E.9 and leaves the brief/plan out of sync with the implementation. If the team now agrees that `07 §6.2` is not citeable under the MUST-only rule, update the plan/review brief/chapter-9 surface accordingly; otherwise the implementation is still missing one planned scenario.

The revised code is materially better. The suite and citation tool both run clean here: `uv run pytest -q conformance/` passed with 86 tests in 48.83s, and `uv run python conformance/src/conformance/tools/check_citations.py` passed with 85 scenario citations. I would not call it fully clear for commit/PR yet because of the remaining partial-startup leak and the still-weaker-than-planned chapter-9 coverage guard.
